data.name: script_instructions.Text
data.value: The script in the next input is used to run the process node after input files and MS files are downloaded. The following script would be run as a batch file or shell command. To facilitate different unique commands for different processing apps, the following symbols are used to represent input/output results: &&output&& means output file; &&input_1&& means inputfile_1; &&input_2&& means inputfile_2, &&loop&& &&raw_file_name&& &&loop&& means loops through each individual raw_file_name/MS file name. the following command: "DiscovererDaemon.exe -c custom - a custom E:\PD_temp\1689.raw - a custom E:\PD_temp\1699.raw - r E:\PD_temp\result.msf - b - e custom ANY E:\PD_temp\1.pdProcessingWF; E:\PD_temp\1.pdConsensusWF"; Would be represented by: "DiscovererDaemon.exe -c custom &&loop&& - a custom &&raw_file_name&& &&loop&& - r &&output&&.msf -b - e custom ANY &&input_1&& &&input_2&&"
